This movie has been hard to track down and find. It should never be lost. This movie, and also Excalibur, came out in the same year, when I was 11 years old, and they both have captivated my imagination since their release. They must be kept alive!

This movie is ripped from original DVD, in DVD format (not re-encoded). I had to compress it to .rar for the site to accept its size. Just uncompress it, place the files in a folder named VIDEO_TS, and your dvd player should read it and play it just fine.
